Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Trim @green beans{6%oz} if necessary.

Trim and discard woody bottom ends from asparagus or cut @broccoli{8%oz} into bite-size pieces if necessary. (Save green beans for another use.)

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a #large bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%oz}, scallion whites, @hoisin sauce{2%tablespoons}, and @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}; season with @salt{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings) and @pepper{}.

Form beef mixture into two 1-inch-tall loaves (four loaves for 4). Place on one side of a lightly oiled #baking sheet{} (for 4, arrange meatloaves across entire sheet).

Roast on top rack for ~{5%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet then).

Once meatloaves have roasted for 5 minutes, carefully remove baking sheet from oven. Brush tops of meatloaves with @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoons}.

On opposite side of sheet, toss green beans and scallion greens with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (For 4 servings, toss green beans on a second sheet.)

Roast on top rack until green beans are tender and browned and meatloaves are cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes} more. (For 4, roast meatloaves on top rack and green beans on middle rack.)

Once meatloaves have roasted 5 minutes, swap in asparagus or broccoli for green beans. Roast ~{10-12%minutes} more for asparagus or ~{15-20%minutes} more for broccoli (if meatloaves are done before broccoli, carefully remove from sheet and continue roasting broccoli).

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoons} and @sriracha{1%teaspoon}. Add water 1 tsp at a time until you reach a drizzling consistency.

Fluff rice with a fork.

Divide meatloaves, rice, and green beans between plates in separate sections. Drizzle Sriracha mayo over green beans and serve.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.